<h2 class="title">Upload Microarray</h2>

<% form_for(@microarray, :html => { :multipart => true }) do |f| %>
  <%= f.error_messages %>

  <p>
    <%= f.label "Select Normal Microarray Dataset" %><br/>
    <%= f.file_field :normal_datafile %>
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <%= f.label "Select Cancer Microarray Dataset" %><br/>
    <%= f.file_field :cancer_datafile %>
  </p>
  
  <p>
    <%= f.submit "Upload" %>
  </p>
<% end %>

<%= link_to 'Cancel', searches_path %>

<div class="clearbox"></div>
<h2 class="title">Microarray File Format</h2>

<p>BioCAD utilizes a simplistic microarray file format structure. 
  Columns represent conditions and rows genes. 
  Cells are separated by a single white-space characters (space or tab).
  </p>
  <p>
  The first column should contain the gene symbols associated with the samples.
  These samples should be ordered the same for both the cancer and normal set.</p>

